  • Classes in Model used by Controller
    Class
    Description
    Intersection
    Intersection is the class that defines a location on the map.
    Map
    Map is the class that defines the city map.
    MapBoundaries
    Boundaries of the map.
    Path
    Path is a list of segments that forms a road from a stop to another one.
    Request
    Request is a pair of stops : A pickup stop. A delivery stop. From several requests, a tour can be computed respecting the constraint that a pickup stop must be visited by the deliverer before its corresponding delivery stop.
    Stop
    Stop inherits Intersection and is an intersection with a duration and will be visited by the deliverer.
    Tour
    Tour implements the interface Observable in order to apply the Observer design pattern.

    Path

    Request
    Request is a pair of stops : A pickup stop. A delivery stop. From several requests, a tour can be computed respecting the constraint that a pickup stop must be visited by the deliverer before its corresponding delivery stop.
    Segment
    Segment is the class representing a road segment.
    A segment is characterized by: A departure intersection which is the origin of the segment. An arrival intersection which is the end of the segment. A length which is the length of the segment in meters. A name which is the name of the segment. Segments are created when loading a map by parsing an XML map file.
    Stop
    Stop inherits Intersection and is an intersection with a duration and will be visited by the deliverer.
